<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="423" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">365.1121 Cimador, Guido/2:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Trieste (<persName type="to">Winslow</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-03T18:00:00-04:00">August
                                        3, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Guido Cimador, naturalized citizen, holder of passport No. 437712
                                dated September 3, 1931, is alleged to have been arrested at Prato
                                Carnico, Udine, on June 3 and to be still in prison.</p>
                            <p>Please render appropriate assistance, telegraph brief report and send
                                full report by pouch.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>